introduced raid exp with it, raid exp would solve every problem.<br><br>There's nothing anyone can do about these things, but I do ask that when you are sitting in some camp with 3 in your group and don't want to let xyz person into your group because it reduces your precious exp, think about why you play the game, I assure you it's not because you can get innate run speed. And I bet it has something to do with friends, and socialization.<br><br>Or, you can just tell me to @#%$ off and go get your 58th AA point......<br><br>Exp is the devil. <p>Pictures are worth a thousand words. Someone asked me to shutup so I took down my picture. Now my posts are all 1000 words less.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubogfatherbellybarsh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bogfather Bellybarsh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Fodder</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/23/02 8:00:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=414.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: General Flame</span><hr size=1> Aye...i agree.  I find it sometimes nigh-on immpossible to find a group, anywhere, though that problem has been slightly aleviated with my obtaining of a seb key.  FG is probably the best example of all.  You go in there, you /shout you're LFG....nothing happens.  You look around.  Everybody's soloing.  Now, I of course have np with soloists, being one myself on occasion, but in the end the zone is just now a Soloist's, or guild-group zone.  You don't get pickup groups - lucky for me I have the occasional mate who levels there I can ask to join - but to those who don't, what happens to them?<br><br>They trawl off to Maidens.  Oops! Nobody there.  Akheva? Group? Maybe, but getting out's the doozy.  Velks? 45 people in there.  Chardok? Nobody's there.  KC? Train! <br><br>Personally, I'd love to see Maidens, Chardok, and Akheva more populated.  Chardok itself holds the illusive metal pipe i, and many other monks need (¬_¬), but because it is only taken once in a blue moon, the pipe is either nigh-on immpossible to get, or very hard to.  Today was actually the first time i've ever seen a group doing the betrayer.  And I've been around 35 times - not exactly great is it?  Because of Chardok being unpopulated, there's now a big bottleneck in the Monk epic, similar (but not quite as bad) to the cleric epic, thanks to the fact that not only have they made the betrayer harder to get to, but it's static.  Superb.  <br><br>And what does this mean?<br>If you don't have the ability to call upon a decent force of people to do exp, or something like the betrayer, you're going to be hard pressed to get the best exp, or that illusive pipe.<br><br>Thank you, this has been a monk rant ~_~ <p><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=80 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame/17.png" ALT="What Video Game Character Are You? I am Mario." /></A>I am <B>Mario</B>.<BR /><BR />I like to jump around, and would lead a fairly serene and aimless existence if it weren't for my friends always getting into trouble. I love to help out, even when it puts me at risk. I seem to make friends with people who just can't stay out of trouble. <A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl">What Video Game Character Are You?</A></TD></TR></TABLE><br>If I was an Autobot, I'd be:<br><a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests"><img border=0  src="http://android5.com/misc/tests/autobot/bluestreak.gif"alt="Click to see what Autobot you could be!"></a><br>Take the <a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests">Transformers personality test</a> at android5.com!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=